entries.femaleVariant: [Get in]
Yo, Miss V. A pleasure.
Mind if I ask you somethin' right off the bangle?
Got a classic tale for ya. Psychogang, doin' its thing two weeks back, jumped a Militech convoy, got away with the gear. Corp don't even know Maelstrom's involved.
Who's the woman?
Who's the prima donna?
Now see, convoy was carryin' the Flathead – a little combat bot, a prototype. And I need me that bit o' high-grade military tech.
Corpo agent, internal affairs. Been skittin' 'round town askin' after the convoy as if her life depended on findin' it. The one lead she got's zip-tied in her trunk.
Royce guy – who is he?
[Take shard]
Heheh. Let's roll.
Hang on. Got a question of my own, now. Why all this, Dex? Why me?
entries.maleVariant: Hang on. I got a question of my own, now. Why all this, Dex? Why me?

entries.femaleVariant: The job – tell me more.
Why meet me? Why the show?
Slot in the shard.
Think I got everything. Time I got to work.
Would you rather live in peace as Miss Nobody, die ripe, old and smellin' slightly of urine? Or go down for all times in a blaze of glory, smellin' near like posies, 'thout seein' your thirtieth?
entries.maleVariant: Would you rather live in peace as Mr. Nobody, die ripe, old and smellin' slightly of urine? Or go down for all times in a blaze of glory, smellin' near like posies, 'thout seein' your thirtieth?

entries.femaleVariant: Call me ol' fashioned, but I like to look anyone I do biz with in the eye.
Had the pleasure of meetin' the Jackster in the past. And sweet T-Bug helped this brother out two years ago. So here we are.
Why, that's just music to my ears. I'll set up the meet with Miss Parker at Lizzie's Bar. Flathead, though, is gonna be all you.
Lemme hear it – what's the job?
There's this… prototype tech – a biochip, to be precise. Job's to grab it. Simple.
Maelstrom – what's the issue?
Client – tell me about her.
What's the issue needs resolving with Maelstrom? Got a beef?
entries.maleVariant: What's the issue needs resolvin' with Maelstrom? Got a beef?

entries.femaleVariant: Know all I need, I think.
Client. What's her thing? Why's she need to meet?
Woman's name's Evelyn Parker. Vettin' her wasn't easy. Put the word out I was lookin' for any kinda intel…
One more thing, Ms. V.
Coulda had Jackie or T-Bug sittin' here. Coulda just done this on comms…
'Sides all that, got a special little pre-mission just for you. But we'll get to that.
Dexter DeShawn in the flesh. Ample, indeed.
Mmh... guessin' it belongs to a corp?
entries.maleVariant: Yeah...? Huh, guessin' it belongs to a corp.

entries.femaleVariant: Mhm – Arasaka.
Surely that's no problem?
Not at all.
That's a death sentence.
Pff. Corps don't deserve special treatment.
entries.maleVariant: Heh. Corps don't deserve special treatment.

entries.femaleVariant: No, no problem. Just a death sentence. NC's Arasaka's turf, nobody fucks with them here.
You work this out? Got a plan?
Shit. Heh, you ain't playin' around.
What can I say, Miss V – high risk, high reward. First rule of the Afterlife.
entries.maleVariant: What can I say, Mr. V – high risk, high reward. First rule of the Afterlife.

entries.femaleVariant: 'Sides that, I'm no leadhead. Ain't gonna leave no trace for them to follow 'cause we gonna do this clean an' on the hush-hush. We understand each other?
Got a feelin' this could be a start of a beautiful friendship built on heaps of eddies.
Two things. First's a conundrum with the Maelstrom boys. Needs active resolvin', that.
Second's a rendezvous. Simple. Client who brought us the job's anxious. She wants to parley with one o' the team.
'Cause if we don't get that bot, we don't get no 'Saka chip. An' we sure as hell don't get no happily-ever-after. But don't get excited, it's a single-use toy.
Stick up her ass ain't growin' any shorter, so she must be gettin' desperate. Be wise to think how you could use that.
Royce guy – what's he like?
A straight psychopath, chrome-lovin' kind.
Big club in this town.
I'll give you that. 'Cept few of its other members, no matter the stakes, would put a friend and associate through an industrial microwave dryer.
Woman's a corp agent?
Corpo agent – what's she playin' at?
Hell if I know. Been skittin' 'round town askin' after the convoy as if her life depended on findin' it. The one lead she got's zip-tied in her trunk.
Mhh... Sounds like she was waitin' on the transport, got stood up. Monochrome in the back's probably her chief suspect.
entries.maleVariant: Sounds like she was waitin' on the transport, got stood up. Monochrome in the back's probably her chief suspect.

entries.femaleVariant: Got nothin' from him or on 'im, so she's keepin' him just in case. But she needs to find the stolen gear before her bosses learn she fucked up.
entries.maleVariant: Got nothin' from him or on him, so she's keepin' 'im just in case. But she needs to find the stolen gear before her bosses learn she fucked up.

entries.femaleVariant: Well, Miss V. That is some impressive deduction. Naturally, use that intel as you please, preferably well.
entries.maleVariant: Well, Mr. V. That is some impressive deduction. Naturally, use that intel as you please, preferably well.

entries.femaleVariant: Yours truly'll be remote, T-Bug ain't no people person, and Jackie's only good at some things – I know you know what I mean. Pretty much leaves you.
Anyway, our lil' client insisted on meetin' someone with skin in the game – you know, who'll be there for it all.
Right, and...?
Some brothers from Pacifica got back to me. Tol' me to stop lookin', end of convo, heheh.
How they remember you – that's all that counts.
Miss Nobodies don't survive in Night City.
entries.maleVariant: Mr. Nobodies don't survive in Night City.

entries.femaleVariant: This some sorta test?
It's first place or no place, Dex. Cost isn't a factor.
You're either somebody or you fizzle out into nothin'. Night City don't let you choose.
This some sorta test?
Y'mean... riddles?
Mh, just a pet topic o' mine.
No, Miss V. Ontology.
Oh, but it does. See, in my line of work I choose to be Mr. Chill. But folk who try to take advantage, well, they see the beast inside…
A'ight, listen close. Scannin' a serious job, now. Plain gargantuan compared to smashin' up a scav haunt.
Huh, classic. I'd expect nothin' less from eager, supple youth. Respect.
Quiet life or blaze o' glory? Hmm?
Later, now.
Apparently, first thing to burst are the eyeballs. Get a nice, clear "pop!" Then the rest goes goulash.
'Course, to do so you'll need that frazzled cat's info. Sendin' it now.
'Course, to do so you'll need that frazzled cat's info. Sending it now.
Now, I flat out purchased the damn thing from Maelstrom. Problem is, I did so from a gent went by the name of Brick.
I say "went" 'cause Brick was the leader. Three days after we'd sealed our deal, his friend and gangmate, one Simon Randall, AKA Royce, plain dropped his ass.
Royce is in charge now. And I got no way of knowin' if he aims to honor his predecessor's word.
To add to this "shitstrom," one Meredith Stout of Militech has developed an interest in said convoy.
[Get out]
